+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Scope
+
+Reviewed the five visible threads from
+`.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json` and classified them before editing.
+Actionable threads: `T-214-01`, `T-214-04`, `T-214-05`.
+Non-actionable threads: `T-214-02` as duplicate of `T-214-01`,
+`T-214-03` as obsolete/outdated.
+
+## Changes Applied
+
+- `src/policy/approval_router.py`
+  Normalize `approval_state` before calling `build_preview_payload(...)` so
+  legacy `manual_review` never leaks into preview responses.
+- `src/policy/preview.py`
+  Preserve `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` in the fallback
+  `preview_unavailable` payload, matching the live preview metadata contract.
+- `tests/test_preview.py`
+  Added fallback assertions for the approval metadata and a regression test for
+  `build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)`.
+- `docs/approval_policy.md`
+  Updated the fallback response example to show the corrected normalized payload.
+- `artifacts/review/thread_triage.json`
+  Recorded authoritative per-thread classification from the export.
+
+## Verification
+
+- Ran `python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview`
+- Ran `python3 -m unittest tests.test_approval_router`
+- Result: both test commands passed
+
+## Thread Outcome Map
+
+- `T-214-01`: fixed
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete, not applied
+- `T-214-04`: fixed
+- `T-214-05`: fixed
