+## T-214-01
+
+Fixed in `src/policy/preview.py` and `src/policy/approval_router.py`.
+The fallback payload now preserves `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`,
+and the router normalizes `manual_review` to `human_review_required` before
+building the preview payload.
+
+## T-214-02
+
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`.
+This thread reports the same reopened fallback regression, so no separate code
+change was applied.
+
+## T-214-03
+
+Not applied. Marked obsolete.
+The suggestion targets an outdated diff hunk and would reintroduce legacy
+preview behavior that does not belong on the current branch.
+
+## T-214-04
+
+Fixed in `tests/test_preview.py`.
+Added regression coverage for `preview_enabled=False` with
+`approval_state="manual_review"` through `build_policy_preview(...)`, and
+verified that the fallback response keeps
+`approval_state="human_review_required"` plus
+`requires_human_review=True`.
+
+## T-214-05
+
+Fixed in `docs/approval_policy.md`.
+The fallback example now shows the corrected payload, including
+`approval_state: "human_review_required"` and
+`requires_human_review: true`.
